1
00:00:03,136 --> 00:00:23,507
I am amused when I look back on my life.

2
00:00:24,690 --> 00:00:26,393
To say I lived it wouldn't be the truth.

3
00:00:27,033 --> 00:00:29,176
To say I did not live it would be a lie.

4
00:00:30,135 --> 00:00:35,100
In the clarity and distance of old age, it seems a tale of another age, another person.

5
00:00:36,222 --> 00:00:38,325
Yet I remember it all as clear as day.

6
00:00:41,027 --> 00:00:47,954
I was born at the beginning of the cold season, the Himalayan wind chilling the dying embers of a warm sun.

7
00:00:49,316 --> 00:00:59,045
My mother rejoiced, of course, as did the household of relatives and friends, but my father was more concerned with my horoscope, and he slipped away with colleagues to study the charts.

8
00:01:00,325 --> 00:01:06,712
That next morning, it was an anxious father who hurried to the palace to fulfil the morning rituals of a royal chaplain.

9
00:01:07,634 --> 00:01:10,216
There he found the king troubled and agitated.

10
00:01:11,578 --> 00:01:16,524
Ah, Gagaji, I was dozing after my evening meal when I woke into a living nightmare.

11
00:01:17,245 --> 00:01:20,028
All my armour was shaking, clattering, flashing.

12
00:01:20,048 --> 00:01:25,674
Oh, that would have been the time Mantani gave birth to our son, Your Majesty, and...

13
00:01:26,667 --> 00:01:30,552
I'm afraid, into an inauspicious constellation.

14
00:01:31,754 --> 00:01:32,474
Inauspicious?

15
00:01:33,316 --> 00:01:35,700
A worried king has no time for sympathetic joy.

16
00:01:35,739 --> 00:01:44,391
There are signs that show great promise indeed, and yet others that indicate something quite terrible.

17
00:01:45,453 --> 00:01:47,115
Something terrible, such as?

18
00:01:47,856 --> 00:01:48,938
The king wanted precision.

19
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,621
I can't say, Your Majesty.

20
00:01:52,543 --> 00:01:55,307
And at the king's growing frustration, he quickly added...

21
00:01:55,944 --> 00:01:58,168
Perhaps it may be prudent to be rid of him.

22
00:01:59,530 --> 00:02:01,072
My life hung on a thread.

23
00:02:02,674 --> 00:02:05,218
Thankfully, this king was not so easily frightened.

24
00:02:05,319 --> 00:02:09,686
Indeed, he was surprised my father should put such little value on my life.

25
00:02:10,747 --> 00:02:12,229
But he's born a Brahmin.

26
00:02:13,050 --> 00:02:20,923
Surely, properly educated and carefully nurtured, he'll overcome any evil tendencies, and that promise will shine through.

27
00:02:23,248 --> 00:02:30,191
This was not the first time I was to owe my life to the compassion of this young, arrogant king, Pasenadi of Kosala.

28
00:02:31,275 --> 00:02:37,073
My parents expressed their uneasy hope in naming me Ahimsaka, the Harmless One.

29
00:02:56,272 --> 00:02:58,575
My childhood was happy and untroubled.

30
00:02:58,936 --> 00:02:59,997
I was my mother's favorite.

31
00:03:00,698 --> 00:03:03,381
I do remember being offered all manner of bribes to be good.

32
00:03:04,081 --> 00:03:05,263
Not that it had much effect.

33
00:03:06,024 --> 00:03:14,052
It seems I had an insatiable desire to chase mosquitoes, cockroaches, frogs, anything that moved, and squash them.

34
00:03:17,235 --> 00:03:21,741
However, there was one extraordinary incident that shook my usual happy composure.

35
00:03:22,514 --> 00:03:26,658
Suddenly, a gang of boys, all friends, playmates, stood around me.

36
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:31,145
One of them, a big boy, Vajiro, began jeering at me.

37
00:03:32,227 --> 00:03:34,408
Creep, think you're better than all of us.

38
00:03:35,129 --> 00:03:35,991
They all joined in.

39
00:03:37,193 --> 00:03:38,514
At first, I thought they were joking.

40
00:03:39,316 --> 00:03:40,637
Then they began to push me around.

41
00:03:42,098 --> 00:03:44,883
All of a sudden, everything went blank.

42
00:03:44,902 --> 00:03:47,866
When I came to my senses, the children were staring at me.

43
00:03:48,548 --> 00:03:50,310
Before me lay Vajiro.

44
00:03:54,306 --> 00:03:55,968
One by one, they sidled away.

45
00:03:57,009 --> 00:04:01,635
When the big boy got up, his blood-stained lips flamed with implacable revenge.

46
00:04:02,257 --> 00:04:03,277
I'll get you for this!

47
00:04:04,961 --> 00:04:06,002
I laughed at his threat.

48
00:04:06,962 --> 00:04:09,506
I felt only the power and grandeur of a conqueror.

49
00:04:10,227 --> 00:04:16,314
But, more ominous, I was savouring the exquisite pleasure of drawing blood.

50
00:04:26,824 --> 00:04:36,898
By young manhood, I was well practised in the arts of war, and it shone such potential in my studies that my father sent me to Takasila, the foremost seat of learning.

51
00:04:38,238 --> 00:04:42,485
Such was my reputation that the most learned teacher wanted to see me.

52
00:04:42,504 --> 00:04:50,074
Agamaha Pandita Abinyana, a small, rotund, elderly man, was revered for his incisive intellect.

53
00:04:51,115 --> 00:04:54,839
That, coupled with a stentorian voice, made him a formidable debater.

54
00:04:56,322 --> 00:05:02,690
He fired all manner of questions at me, jabbing them at me with his little finger that seemed to turn them into sharp needles.

55
00:05:03,331 --> 00:05:05,896
It was a trait that was to take on a sinister meaning for me.

56
00:05:06,956 --> 00:05:12,365
You'll outshine them all, even me, he announced with great delight.

57
00:05:14,548 --> 00:05:16,610
I felt a great devotion to my guru.

58
00:05:17,713 --> 00:05:21,418
I began to treat him with a special veneration due to a natural father.

59
00:05:22,545 --> 00:05:25,149
I felt sure he saw me equally as a natural son.

60
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:31,519
It was my devotion to learning and a desire to please my guru that caused me to excel.

61
00:05:33,701 --> 00:05:40,891
Then, one day, I remember it too well, he glanced at me in a way that greatly disturbed me.

62
00:05:41,913 --> 00:05:47,701
There was suspicion in his eyes, a tightness to his face suggesting fear, or was it hatred?

63
00:05:49,264 --> 00:05:52,468
As the days passed, he grew more and more distant.

64
00:05:54,608 --> 00:05:58,574
During the final days, there were awkward silences and false smiles.

65
00:05:59,894 --> 00:06:01,757
I felt hurt by our loss of intimacy.

66
00:06:02,658 --> 00:06:04,281
Too confused to ask what the matter was.

67
00:06:05,803 --> 00:06:10,651
Anyway, I decided to put it all to one side, especially so since my final exams were starting.

68
00:06:11,312 --> 00:06:14,115
The recitations, the public debates, the competitive games.

69
00:06:15,577 --> 00:06:16,559
I performed very well.

70
00:06:17,259 --> 00:06:20,785
In fact, I was acclaimed foremost student of my year.

71
00:06:22,807 --> 00:06:27,172
On the very day the results were given, my deepest anxieties were confirmed.

72
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:29,714
My guru called me to see him.

73
00:06:30,555 --> 00:06:31,516
I expected praise.

74
00:06:32,216 --> 00:06:36,622
I wanted to express my unrepairable gratitude, and indeed that's what I did.

75
00:06:38,004 --> 00:06:46,252
But then he said, You know, it is the duty of every student to offer a gift of homage to their guru.

76
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:48,574
Oh, indeed, I exclaimed.

77
00:06:49,096 --> 00:06:50,096
Name it, Guruji.

78
00:06:51,375 --> 00:06:55,380
What he asked for came as an utter shock.

79
00:06:55,401 --> 00:07:02,269
For him, sir cop, he said with absolute authority, bring me a little figure of one hundred people.

80
00:07:04,812 --> 00:07:06,574
His eyes demanded obedience.

81
00:07:08,757 --> 00:07:12,261
I can't do that, I remember stuttering.

82
00:07:12,281 --> 00:07:15,425
He was silent, his glare insisting submission.

83
00:07:16,386 --> 00:07:18,108
My family are all Brahmins.

84
00:07:18,507 --> 00:07:20,690
We live as harmlessly as possible.

85
00:07:20,992 --> 00:07:25,920
to the highest standards of one who is born of the mouth of Brahma.

86
00:07:25,939 --> 00:07:33,673
Those who refuse to pay the ceremonial gift of homage, a sacred duty to their guru, are to be detested.

87
00:07:34,454 --> 00:07:38,060
Such a person tramples on our time-honored tradition.

88
00:07:38,081 --> 00:07:41,065
All their learning will produce but sterile fruit.

89
00:07:42,168 --> 00:07:46,053
Is this the behavior of a son born of the mouth of Brahma?

90
00:07:47,839 --> 00:07:52,064
There was an inexplicable hardness to his tone, a sneer in his question.

91
00:07:53,165 --> 00:07:54,367
I simply had no response.

92
00:07:55,889 --> 00:07:58,612
I bowed, mumbling that I would follow his wishes.

93
00:08:00,334 --> 00:08:02,916
When I looked up, he'd turned away and was calling for his servant.

94
00:08:04,399 --> 00:08:06,521
I backed away, cowed and confused.

95
00:08:07,281 --> 00:08:11,666
The guru had a right to name his gift of homage, but why was mine so terrible?

96
00:08:12,468 --> 00:08:14,630
Why had he not asked similar of others?

97
00:08:15,110 --> 00:08:17,374
All he asked of them was fruit, clothing, medicine.

98
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:21,824
That night I fell into a heavy, disturbed sleep.

99
00:08:22,826 --> 00:08:24,548
I woke into a terrible night terror.

100
00:08:25,290 --> 00:08:28,495
Pointed fingers like darts burst upon me from every angle.

101
00:08:28,836 --> 00:08:31,982
I fought furiously with sword and shield, writhing in agony.

102
00:08:33,605 --> 00:08:42,399
When I came to my senses, I was lying on the floor, soaked in cold sweat and shaking, awake to the full horror of my duty.

103
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:52,932
In a daze, I got my belongings together and began to make my way homeward, a journey of two weeks or more, time to clear my head and cool my heart.

104
00:08:54,615 --> 00:09:01,804
I stayed in the villages en route, hardly talking to anyone, and all the time I was convincing myself of my duty.

105
00:09:03,486 --> 00:09:05,990
I must get 100 fingers.

106
00:09:07,878 --> 00:09:10,140
How else could I possibly do so without killing?

107
00:09:10,761 --> 00:09:13,666
People aren't just going to let me walk off with their little finger.

108
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:15,448
I have to kill.

109
00:09:15,469 --> 00:09:17,471
There's no other way.

110
00:09:17,491 --> 00:09:19,193
Such killing isn't murder.

111
00:09:19,234 --> 00:09:21,918
I have to fulfil my sacred duty.

112
00:09:22,379 --> 00:09:24,662
Who am I to renounce a time-honoured tradition?

113
00:09:24,721 --> 00:09:26,144
I have to do it.

114
00:09:26,264 --> 00:09:27,186
I have to.

115
00:09:34,506 --> 00:09:44,538
In this way, by the time I arrived at the dark and dense Jarlini forest on the border of my country, Kosala, I was steeled for my first killing.

116
00:09:51,307 --> 00:09:56,673
I found a cave on a hill that looked down on a stretch of road travelled by hunters, gatherers and merchants.

117
00:09:58,456 --> 00:10:03,601
Water and forest food, banana, mango, rich papaya, various nuts, were all in abundance.

118
00:10:04,222 --> 00:10:05,624
And I spent my first day.

119
00:10:07,986 --> 00:10:19,639
That evening, in the pearl-white silence of a full moon, soft with the scuffing of cicadas, I dug a fire pit to Kali Durga, Divine Mother, womb of all creation.

120
00:10:21,061 --> 00:10:28,087
It was into this cremation ground that I would offer the flesh of my victims to gain them her protection and so sanctify my deeds.

121
00:10:29,215 --> 00:10:34,883
I cut my little finger and into the sacrificial fire I offered my blood as libation.

122
00:10:36,806 --> 00:10:40,931
Staring at the flames, I then began to develop a fierce concentration.

123
00:10:41,972 --> 00:10:44,436
It was going to take all the courage and strength I could muster.

124
00:10:45,157 --> 00:10:49,964
For all my battle skills, I'd never yet killed an animal, never mind a human being.

125
00:10:53,629 --> 00:10:58,075
In the dark dawn of early morning, I rubbed the sacred ash into my body

126
00:10:59,067 --> 00:11:02,792
Filled with religious confidence, I made my way down to the path.

127
00:11:04,193 --> 00:11:05,216
There I hid, waiting.

128
00:11:06,717 --> 00:11:12,966
And sure enough, in that early hour, the shuffle of a wood-gatherer with his hacks and bundles of rope.

129
00:11:15,029 --> 00:11:21,339
I'd imagined a swift dagger attack from behind, but instead pulled an arrow into the bow, a more easy prey there couldn't be.

130
00:11:23,562 --> 00:11:25,884
But I couldn't let that arrow fly.

131
00:11:28,125 --> 00:11:33,554
I continued to stalk him, all the time urging myself to fulfil my duty.

132
00:11:33,576 --> 00:11:39,385
And anyway, what had life left for this old, feeble man but a miserable diseased end?

133
00:11:39,405 --> 00:11:42,912
It was a mercy to kill him.

134
00:11:42,932 --> 00:11:44,654
I took a deep breath.

135
00:11:44,674 --> 00:11:46,557
As quick as lightning, I thrusted my sword.

136
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:49,864
It seemed to penetrate like a knife through butter.

137
00:11:51,177 --> 00:11:56,182
His body startled, tensed, and suddenly slumped, dragging me downwards, so I tumbled onto him.

138
00:11:57,062 --> 00:11:58,225
There I looked into his face.

139
00:11:59,346 --> 00:12:02,129
His eyes glazed, empty and deaf.

140
00:12:02,889 --> 00:12:06,894
His mouth wide open, locked in shock.

141
00:12:06,913 --> 00:12:09,976
Horrified, I leapt up, hardly able to catch my breath.

142
00:12:11,658 --> 00:12:13,380
Suddenly, there were great cries.

143
00:12:13,861 --> 00:12:17,826
When a small crowd of men were racing towards me, their axes shaking in the air.

144
00:12:18,532 --> 00:12:20,134
All went blank.

145
00:12:20,153 --> 00:12:25,701
I remember nothing but standing there with these same men strewn around me, twisted and bleeding.

146
00:12:27,722 --> 00:12:32,708
As I realized what had happened, there came upon me that strange feeling of omnipotence.

147
00:12:33,811 --> 00:12:38,797
I stood towering above the slain bodies, the skill, the power, the glory of it.

148
00:12:40,658 --> 00:12:45,784
Like the all-conquering hero, I sliced off each little finger with a flourish.

149
00:12:47,106 --> 00:12:48,268
And I rejoiced.

150
00:12:49,226 --> 00:12:49,807
I've done it.

151
00:12:50,368 --> 00:12:50,828
I've done it.

152
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:53,150
And it's easy, so easy.

153
00:12:53,211 --> 00:12:56,414
I danced for joy and relief.

154
00:12:59,337 --> 00:13:00,700
I then hid the bodies.

155
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:04,864
The more I could keep the killings secret, the easier would I capture my victims.

156
00:13:07,527 --> 00:13:08,508
I returned to my cave.

157
00:13:09,168 --> 00:13:13,293
There I cut what flesh I could from the fingers into the sacrificial pyre.

158
00:13:13,994 --> 00:13:17,697
I then threaded the bones with vine and tied them onto a branch.

159
00:13:18,421 --> 00:13:26,851
Once they were picked clean by birds or ants, I'd hang it around my neck as a divine amulet.

160
00:13:26,871 --> 00:13:29,655
Late that same afternoon, I heard in the distance a calling.

161
00:13:30,496 --> 00:13:33,541
Names being called by many over and over again.

162
00:13:34,461 --> 00:13:35,984
Intrigued, I went down.

163
00:13:37,004 --> 00:13:40,750
Of course, family and friends had come to look for the wood gatherers.

164
00:13:42,231 --> 00:13:44,754
Again I stalked and pounced like a tiger.

165
00:13:45,315 --> 00:13:49,018
My attacks were swift and smooth, the blows of death precise, clean.

166
00:13:49,899 --> 00:13:56,225
Having taken the fingers of two men, moving around a bamboo coppice, there in front of me three women.

167
00:13:57,666 --> 00:13:58,767
Yes, I stopped.

168
00:13:59,027 --> 00:14:00,148
For a moment there was doubt.

169
00:14:01,149 --> 00:14:03,591
I felt something tight against my heart.

170
00:14:05,153 --> 00:14:06,594
But by now I was too committed.

171
00:14:07,335 --> 00:14:08,995
Two were dead before the other could turn.

172
00:14:09,876 --> 00:14:12,019
She stared at me, paralysed in fear.

173
00:14:13,197 --> 00:14:18,285
and that was the face that fell into the embrace of soft grasses and wild flowers.

174
00:14:19,649 --> 00:14:20,610
Did I feel pity?

175
00:14:21,731 --> 00:14:21,952
None.

176
00:14:22,955 --> 00:14:24,537
I was drunk with conquest.

177
00:14:27,062 --> 00:14:30,948
I could have easily killed the rest, but for a scream of horror some distance from me.

178
00:14:32,051 --> 00:14:34,755
I was moving so fast I hadn't bothered to hide the bodies.

179
00:14:34,975 --> 00:14:35,998
The game was up.

180
00:14:36,332 --> 00:14:39,758
It was now a matter of stopping the news travelling beyond the village.

181
00:14:40,678 --> 00:14:43,842
I ran at maddening speed until I arrived at a large clearing.

182
00:14:44,403 --> 00:14:49,631
Many buildings nestled there among the palm trees, the place littered with busy chickens and scrawny dogs.

183
00:14:50,231 --> 00:14:55,639
I was sure that once the villagers returned, they'd send a party off to the king at Savathi.

184
00:14:57,361 --> 00:14:59,666
It was on that road I lay waiting.

185
00:15:00,826 --> 00:15:04,972
And sure enough, a handful of men came bearing the usual crude weapons.

186
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:10,730
I followed them till they had gone quite some way from the village and well out of earshot.

187
00:15:12,173 --> 00:15:16,802
It was then, full of the courage of invincibility, I punched on them.

188
00:15:17,484 --> 00:15:19,489
None of this low caste would have had my training.

189
00:15:20,451 --> 00:15:21,854
It was all becoming too easy.

190
00:15:23,798 --> 00:15:26,082
I decided to take full advantage of the situation.

191
00:15:26,687 --> 00:15:40,004
I made my way back to the village, and in the early hours of the following morning, just when colour begins to seep into the shades, I crept into the first one-room hut, the air hot and stale with the exhausted slumber of grief.

192
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:47,134
Husband and wife lay together, the children seven, or maybe eight of them, snuggled in the opposite corner.

193
00:15:48,636 --> 00:15:52,662
Their pitiful defencelessness couldn't soften my cruel resolve.

194
00:15:53,519 --> 00:15:56,243
I bathed myself in the blood of carnage.

195
00:15:56,322 --> 00:15:59,528
First the man, then the woman, then the children.

196
00:16:00,769 --> 00:16:03,974
Quietly and speedily, I slit their throats and stabbed their hearts.

197
00:16:05,596 --> 00:16:08,200
And so I savaged hut after hut.

198
00:16:09,402 --> 00:16:13,248
I could see streamlets of blood pick their way down the slope towards the well.

199
00:16:15,951 --> 00:16:22,581
Suddenly, as I left a large wooden house, a scream, I lurched back inside and grabbed that child by the throat.

200
00:16:23,287 --> 00:16:24,308
A rage took me.

201
00:16:24,950 --> 00:16:36,888
I lifted the little body until it dangled in the air, its little arms flailing, mouth agape, eyes bulging in terror, its tiny figures wrenched into my hand, its little feet booting the air.

202
00:16:37,788 --> 00:16:44,799
My grip tightened till the tiny body seized and fell limp.

203
00:16:44,820 --> 00:16:48,044
I stared at that beautiful little face as in a trance.

204
00:16:49,586 --> 00:16:51,690
I couldn't bear to acknowledge what I'd done.

205
00:16:53,256 --> 00:16:58,341
As I dropped the body to continue the slaughter, it was the one finger I left behind.

206
00:17:00,504 --> 00:17:02,865
But that little child's cry had stirred the village.

207
00:17:03,706 --> 00:17:07,970
It was only because of the poor light that I was able to disappear unseen into the forest.

208
00:17:10,873 --> 00:17:13,015
I arrived back at my hideout, exhausted.

209
00:17:14,096 --> 00:17:16,377
As I lay down, the child's face returned.

210
00:17:17,980 --> 00:17:21,643
I turned on my side and slept through the heat of midday.

211
00:17:24,172 --> 00:17:28,859
Late that afternoon, I woke refreshed and of a sudden decided to hunt animals.

212
00:17:30,522 --> 00:17:33,828
Each kill reaffirmed my command over life and death.

213
00:17:34,150 --> 00:17:39,598
In the cool of that evening, for the first time in my life, I sank my teeth into roasted boar.

214
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:41,522
It was delicious.

215
00:17:43,165 --> 00:17:44,407
Again, I rejoiced.

216
00:17:45,788 --> 00:17:47,349
Soon I'll have my hundred fingers.

217
00:17:47,671 --> 00:17:48,612
The debt will be paid.

218
00:17:48,971 --> 00:17:54,019
I'll return home in secret triumph and through my father's good offices enter into the service of the king.

219
00:17:54,660 --> 00:18:04,093
I'll marry a beautiful girl, inherit the farm, have many children, and my life will be a rolling countryside of nothing but contentment and joy.

220
00:18:04,113 --> 00:18:06,656
I danced in joy.

221
00:18:06,876 --> 00:18:08,078
I danced in gratitude.

222
00:18:09,119 --> 00:18:12,825
I danced for Kali, my divine protectoress.

223
00:18:15,319 --> 00:18:17,701
The following morning I woke in more sombre mood.

224
00:18:18,643 --> 00:18:21,987
I realised that even now a platoon of soldiers would be searching for me.

225
00:18:22,886 --> 00:18:28,913
There was only one thing for it, to keep on the move without coherent plan and to range as far as possible.

226
00:18:29,814 --> 00:18:36,000
In this way I could attack unwary travellers along any road, enter any unsuspecting village in the dark.

227
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:39,703
The kill was easy so long as it remained unexpected.

228
00:18:40,183 --> 00:18:42,405
Even the soldiers were useless defence.

229
00:18:42,426 --> 00:18:44,989
Such was their clatter, I could always hear them coming.

230
00:18:47,990 --> 00:18:56,118
On one such outing, I overheard a conversation that first made me laugh, and then showed me to what depravity I had descended.

231
00:18:57,320 --> 00:19:01,925
I heard a small crowd talking about this madman who murdered for little fingers.

232
00:19:02,846 --> 00:19:04,868
A demon, Angulimala.

233
00:19:05,951 --> 00:19:06,310
Me?

234
00:19:07,311 --> 00:19:10,655
I was Angulimala, Garland of Fingers.

235
00:19:11,767 --> 00:19:18,817
Returning that evening, I caught my face in a pool of water... and what I saw truly shocked me.

236
00:19:19,699 --> 00:19:27,549
My black hair was tortured, spikes around my head... my face hidden beneath a matted, grubby beard.

237
00:19:27,569 --> 00:19:28,912
My eyes seemed to bulge.

238
00:19:29,792 --> 00:19:34,480
My lips and tongue, blood red from betel leaf... which I chewed to calm my nerves.

239
00:19:35,461 --> 00:19:39,326
My clothes, torn, filthy and bespattered with human blood...

240
00:19:39,931 --> 00:19:43,234
And there, around my neck, the garland of fingers.

241
00:19:45,076 --> 00:19:47,278
Yes, a demon.

242
00:19:47,298 --> 00:19:50,682
A yucca.

243
00:19:50,702 --> 00:19:57,130
Over this period of but a few weeks, as I gathered my tally of fingers, my bloodlust consumed me.

244
00:19:58,111 --> 00:19:59,251
My dreams were full of it.

245
00:19:59,952 --> 00:20:01,253
Daydreams addicted to it.

246
00:20:01,714 --> 00:20:06,420
To see the horror in their eyes, to hear their screams, was my joy.

247
00:20:08,122 --> 00:20:09,262
Yes, I remember...

248
00:20:10,711 --> 00:20:13,675
I remember it all, as clear as day.

249
00:20:23,051 --> 00:20:31,487
I had now but one finger to go, and I thought to come full circle and return to the very spot on that road where I'd stabbed that poor old wood-gatherer.

250
00:20:32,934 --> 00:20:44,689
Then at last I would present this blood homage to my guru, against whom I'd built up a healthy hatred and often plotted how to avenge my humiliation.

251
00:20:44,709 --> 00:20:47,271
As I hid in waiting, I began to hear a calling.

252
00:20:48,413 --> 00:20:50,256
Oh, my heart jumped into my throat.

253
00:20:51,637 --> 00:20:51,938
Amy!

254
00:20:52,959 --> 00:20:53,339
Amy!

255
00:20:53,380 --> 00:20:55,021
My mother!

256
00:20:55,823 --> 00:20:57,944
My mother calling me as she'd always done.

257
00:20:58,605 --> 00:20:59,988
How could she have known it was me?

258
00:21:00,608 --> 00:21:01,710
Her mother's intuition...

259
00:21:03,682 --> 00:21:07,827
Mother or no, there raged inside me a desire to kill.

260
00:21:09,150 --> 00:21:18,083
A loud, clear no arose, yet against my will my legs began to move nearer and nearer until I saw her.

261
00:21:18,103 --> 00:21:18,865
I couldn't stop.

262
00:21:18,884 --> 00:21:22,470
I just kept advancing, my hand now taking the sword from the scabbard.

263
00:21:23,290 --> 00:21:29,200
I was all but ready to pounce when a tall, bald-headed monk suddenly appeared.

264
00:21:31,356 --> 00:21:33,378
My mother bowed to him.

265
00:21:33,398 --> 00:21:37,844
He must have said something to her, for my mother turned and walked back the way she came.

266
00:21:39,566 --> 00:21:41,106
He then continued along the road.

267
00:21:41,948 --> 00:21:43,789
I was intrigued.

268
00:21:43,809 --> 00:21:50,176
I began to stalk this monk, moving faster and faster, yet the faster I moved, he seemed to be the same distance away.

269
00:21:51,617 --> 00:21:56,022
Finally, frustrated, I burst out of my hiding into the road and ran towards him.

270
00:21:56,303 --> 00:21:58,005
Faster and faster I ran, yet

271
00:21:58,288 --> 00:21:59,710
never getting any closer.

272
00:22:00,351 --> 00:22:03,273
He kept on walking at the very same easy pace.

273
00:22:04,934 --> 00:22:07,678
Finally exhausted, I shouted out, Stop!

274
00:22:08,838 --> 00:22:09,279
And he did.

275
00:22:10,641 --> 00:22:17,907
While I panted, he turned round, quite unhurriedly, and replied, I have stopped, Angulimala.

276
00:22:19,229 --> 00:22:22,211
It's you who haven't stopped.

277
00:22:22,231 --> 00:22:25,134
I was full of rage and yet taken aback.

278
00:22:26,375 --> 00:22:27,537
He was smiling at me.

279
00:22:29,170 --> 00:22:31,573
we stood facing each other for what seemed a long time.

280
00:22:32,953 --> 00:22:45,568
Finally, my curiosity, at his supernatural ability to walk faster than I could run, his obvious fearlessness, and this strange reply brought the student out of me.

281
00:22:45,588 --> 00:22:47,230
''You've stopped, but I haven't!''

282
00:22:47,590 --> 00:22:48,491
I shouted angrily.

283
00:22:50,294 --> 00:22:57,102
''This vicious craving and enjoyment in making others suffer, do you think it will end with your hundred fingers?''

284
00:22:57,772 --> 00:22:59,414
with the murder of your own mother.

285
00:23:00,556 --> 00:23:01,217
I was dumb.

286
00:23:01,257 --> 00:23:05,321
And the consequences, the karma.

287
00:23:05,781 --> 00:23:08,545
Don't you believe the torturer reaps in kind?

288
00:23:09,807 --> 00:23:10,528
Of course I did.

289
00:23:11,228 --> 00:23:15,413
Do harm, and surely harm will follow as a cart follows the ox.

290
00:23:17,115 --> 00:23:22,161
I'm fulfilling an ancient obligation to my guru, I offered in defense.

291
00:23:22,444 --> 00:23:23,185
"'Ha!

292
00:23:23,205 --> 00:23:24,788
Put yourself in the place of your victims.

293
00:23:24,807 --> 00:23:32,096
"'How would you like to be murdered, "'just so that some bright young Brahmin "'can offer your little finger as a present to his guru?'

294
00:23:32,116 --> 00:23:36,482
"'The absurdity of my position hit me like a bolt of lightning.

295
00:23:36,923 --> 00:23:40,086
"'Why had it never occurred to me to take the victim's point of view?'

296
00:23:40,107 --> 00:23:43,111
"'So come then,' he said.

297
00:23:43,131 --> 00:23:44,814
"'You may as well finish the job.'

298
00:23:45,554 --> 00:23:46,395
"'He offered his hand.

299
00:23:46,976 --> 00:23:48,238
"'You needn't kill me for it.'

300
00:23:50,059 --> 00:23:52,282
"'I stared at him in disbelief.'

301
00:23:52,634 --> 00:23:59,526
He was a big man beyond his prime, but still strong enough to defend himself, offering me his little finger.

302
00:24:00,828 --> 00:24:04,115
His fearless act of generosity made my own courage seem puny.

303
00:24:05,457 --> 00:24:08,221
You've been amazingly stupid, he continued.

304
00:24:08,722 --> 00:24:10,145
What happened to your common sense?

305
00:24:10,787 --> 00:24:14,794
It just goes to show how brilliance can service the most ludicrous delusions.

306
00:24:15,752 --> 00:24:27,186
That, not to despair, that very dedication to your studies, and indeed to your murderings, is a virtue that will help perfect contentment even in this very life.

307
00:24:29,430 --> 00:24:33,555
His compassion had utterly exposed my callous logic.

308
00:24:34,695 --> 00:24:37,279
The full horror of what I had done was upon me.

309
00:24:37,819 --> 00:24:42,486
I could hardly bear to look into his kindly yet penetrating eyes.

310
00:24:43,528 --> 00:24:45,931
He indeed was a guru of another kind.

311
00:24:52,699 --> 00:24:54,460
He asked me to take him to my hideout.

312
00:24:55,902 --> 00:24:59,404
We talked of how we'd both been brought up in the lap of luxury.

313
00:25:00,006 --> 00:25:04,330
He, the son of Suddhodana, king of the Saka, north of my own country.

314
00:25:05,412 --> 00:25:08,575
How even as a young man he'd become weary of courtly life.

315
00:25:09,904 --> 00:25:13,711
how he had an insatiable hunger to know the true destiny of a human being.

316
00:25:14,432 --> 00:25:21,221
Were we to wander around aimlessly from life to life, suffering this, enjoying that, or was it simply death, annihilation?

317
00:25:22,544 --> 00:25:23,545
Or was there something else?

318
00:25:26,189 --> 00:25:28,152
On the way I came across some jungle fowl.

319
00:25:28,232 --> 00:25:32,018
I grabbed an arrow, only to feel acute embarrassment.

320
00:25:32,499 --> 00:25:34,301
Such was his immediate effect upon me.

321
00:25:35,644 --> 00:25:37,886
I returned to gathering fruits and nuts.

322
00:25:39,115 --> 00:25:42,358
That midday, we ate together in silence.

323
00:25:44,882 --> 00:25:48,185
It was late afternoon when I woke from a heavy sleep.

324
00:25:48,205 --> 00:25:51,029
Suddenly, seeing the monk again, I jumped and grabbed my dagger.

325
00:25:51,971 --> 00:25:54,013
He chuckled at my ferocious posturing.

326
00:25:54,934 --> 00:25:59,840
Angulimala, when will you again be Ahimsaka, the harmless one?

327
00:26:06,976 --> 00:26:13,365
He asked me to sit in meditation with him, just observe and feel anything that comes into your attention.

328
00:26:15,229 --> 00:26:17,092
I couldn't sit for long, I was so restless.

329
00:26:18,354 --> 00:26:25,845
Walk up and down, slowly, he said, but again, just to be aware of any thoughts and feelings.

330
00:26:25,865 --> 00:26:29,431
I would sit and walk in fits and starts, I just couldn't stand still.

331
00:26:31,013 --> 00:26:34,519
Patience, he said, this is going to take some time.

332
00:26:34,886 --> 00:26:38,011
Don't worry, I'll stay with you till your future is clear.

333
00:26:39,574 --> 00:26:41,616
I immediately relaxed with this assurance.

334
00:26:43,619 --> 00:26:46,564
It took a few days to calm down enough to sit still and watch.

335
00:26:47,905 --> 00:26:50,390
Again and again, I re-enacted my killings.

336
00:26:51,571 --> 00:26:57,701
Endlessly working over the same old themes, the chase, the battle, the kill, and always the excitement, the enjoyment.

337
00:26:58,060 --> 00:26:59,763
I couldn't stop them dominating me.

338
00:27:01,364 --> 00:27:03,787
Don't indulge these fantasies, he warned.

339
00:27:04,127 --> 00:27:07,071
Take away their nourishment and they'll simply die away.

340
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,675
Or else they'll drive you to further atrocity.

341
00:27:10,436 --> 00:27:11,397
And where will it all end?

342
00:27:11,458 --> 00:27:12,880
The king's prison?

343
00:27:13,340 --> 00:27:14,603
To be publicly tortured?

344
00:27:16,144 --> 00:27:17,948
That sent a cold shiver up my spine.

345
00:27:19,809 --> 00:27:26,078
And, he added, undermine these overpowering cravings by considering how much your victims suffered.

346
00:27:28,102 --> 00:27:28,823
That was hard.

347
00:27:30,202 --> 00:27:34,807
I still wanted to justify myself, make light of their suffering.

348
00:27:34,827 --> 00:27:44,297
Disheartened and weary, I stretched and looked into the dark emptiness of a starlit night, and there caught the first delicate arc of the new moon.

349
00:27:45,958 --> 00:27:53,085
I decided to meditate just once more, as if by magic the focus of my fantasies began to change.

350
00:27:54,026 --> 00:27:56,868
Instead of relishing the chaser and the kill,

351
00:27:58,856 --> 00:28:01,701
I began to see the pain and panic of my victims.

352
00:28:03,201 --> 00:28:05,565
It was with these images that I fell asleep.

353
00:28:07,488 --> 00:28:09,911
It was still dark when I felt a hand rock my shoulder.

354
00:28:10,250 --> 00:28:11,172
I woke with a start.

355
00:28:12,273 --> 00:28:13,555
Continue, he said.

356
00:28:14,375 --> 00:28:16,198
He must have felt the change in my heart.

357
00:28:17,420 --> 00:28:17,759
Get up.

358
00:28:18,381 --> 00:28:19,803
Shake off the sloth of sleep.

359
00:28:21,164 --> 00:28:26,451
The voice was sharp, but his smile completely disarmed my angry indignation.

360
00:28:29,401 --> 00:28:31,463
I had by now unwittingly become a disciple.

361
00:28:32,065 --> 00:28:33,707
Like any good student, I obeyed.

362
00:28:35,128 --> 00:28:38,252
I splashed water on my face and began to sit in meditation.

363
00:28:40,256 --> 00:28:49,288
And there they came, the faces tortured in pain, weeping and pleading, vivid and alive as if from the dead.

364
00:28:51,612 --> 00:28:53,535
I began to feel their agonies.

365
00:28:54,780 --> 00:28:57,565
and there held up a remorse that began to shake my body.

366
00:28:58,266 --> 00:29:04,875
Till it started to release, first in little spurts, then in cries, and then in loud moaning and weeping.

367
00:29:06,258 --> 00:29:08,741
I cried and cried and cried.

368
00:29:10,163 --> 00:29:12,606
I felt my very insides were gouged out.

369
00:29:14,911 --> 00:29:17,835
Who knows how long I filled that jungle with my wailing.

370
00:29:20,109 --> 00:29:22,031
Excellent, said the monk, smiling.

371
00:29:22,051 --> 00:29:24,835
Only when true remorse arises can the heart begin to heal.

372
00:29:24,855 --> 00:29:30,080
I did find his joy in my discomfort a little disconcerting.

373
00:29:32,644 --> 00:29:38,049
The images of my cruelty continued to haunt my every meditation, my every action, my every dream.

374
00:29:38,770 --> 00:29:41,834
Every moment was shame, guilt and remorse.

375
00:29:42,974 --> 00:29:44,537
And I was so angry with myself.

376
00:29:45,637 --> 00:29:49,762
Why had I not seen the sheer idiocy of my guru's request?

377
00:29:51,160 --> 00:29:53,943
The gall I felt when I realized I could have said no.

378
00:29:53,983 --> 00:30:00,373
What had stopped me but vile servitude to custom, enslavement to tradition?

379
00:30:02,256 --> 00:30:05,840
And how was I ever going to compensate for such monstrous crimes?

380
00:30:06,962 --> 00:30:10,929
My remorse turned to despair when I saw they were too terrible to be forgiven.

381
00:30:12,851 --> 00:30:15,575
How can we compensate for murder of all things?

382
00:30:16,076 --> 00:30:17,438
this gentle monk asked.

383
00:30:18,413 --> 00:30:22,078
What could replace the loss of grandparents, husband, wife, children?

384
00:30:22,779 --> 00:30:25,964
In such a case, we must simply bear the consequences.

385
00:30:26,105 --> 00:30:26,826
Isn't that enough?

386
00:30:27,487 --> 00:30:29,391
Do we have to punish ourselves as well?

387
00:30:31,794 --> 00:30:35,721
I began to realize that in the end, I would have to give myself up to the authorities.

388
00:30:36,701 --> 00:30:39,125
They would mete out a terrible, tortuous death.

389
00:30:40,107 --> 00:30:44,775
My identity would be revealed, my family shamed and ruined, my mother...

390
00:30:46,375 --> 00:31:04,357
Oh, better for me to live wild, or go to another country far away, take my chances with uncivilised tribes, or better still, to commit suicide, secretly, somewhere the body would be eaten by wild animals, so that I remained anonymous.

391
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,443
He listened to my ranting and raving.

392
00:31:08,884 --> 00:31:11,067
Then again, in a moment of calmness...

393
00:31:12,193 --> 00:31:16,519
Do you want to be a fugitive or live like an animal all your life?

394
00:31:17,461 --> 00:31:20,523
And having murdered so many people, you now want to murder yourself?

395
00:31:20,924 --> 00:31:22,507
Is there no end to your stupidity?

396
00:31:24,189 --> 00:31:29,154
Past deeds cannot be altered, and they will produce present and future consequence.

397
00:31:29,596 --> 00:31:33,881
The true question is, do you have the courage to face it, to suffer it?

398
00:31:34,801 --> 00:31:37,746
For this is the only way you can drain the past of its effect.

399
00:31:40,442 --> 00:31:42,144
His eyes looked steadily into mine.

400
00:31:42,525 --> 00:31:43,046
I jumped up.

401
00:31:43,306 --> 00:31:43,946
I had to walk.

402
00:31:44,607 --> 00:31:48,031
The arguments went round and round, but the truth stood out.

403
00:31:49,012 --> 00:31:51,055
It was better to face the consequences.

404
00:31:53,097 --> 00:31:55,079
Surely the king would have sympathy for me.

405
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,801
He'd known me since I was a baby.

406
00:31:56,862 --> 00:31:58,384
We'd even wrestled each other.

407
00:31:58,844 --> 00:32:01,146
He would understand my dilemma.

408
00:32:01,166 --> 00:32:03,750
What else could a disciple do but obey his guru?

409
00:32:04,726 --> 00:32:07,608
There was my father's influence, the standing of my family.

410
00:32:07,848 --> 00:32:12,773
Indeed, I could defend myself before the king as I defended my actions to my own self.

411
00:32:13,315 --> 00:32:18,980
And if I was shown no mercy, well, then I would have to suffer the consequences.

412
00:32:19,641 --> 00:32:24,526
At least, as this teacher says, I'd wipe the slate clean.

413
00:32:24,546 --> 00:32:27,930
I returned and told him of my decision to give myself up to the authorities.

414
00:32:29,391 --> 00:32:30,952
He nodded, as if in approval.

415
00:32:32,182 --> 00:32:35,086
There was a long silence in which we gazed into each other's eyes.

416
00:32:35,425 --> 00:32:43,017
Then he said, Would you not rather put an end to this whole weary round of births and deaths?

417
00:32:44,759 --> 00:32:45,641
Is there an escape?

418
00:32:45,921 --> 00:32:46,362
I asked.

419
00:32:47,603 --> 00:32:52,809
His face shone with a smile, and he spoke with that absolute assurance of one who knows.

420
00:32:54,932 --> 00:32:58,999
There is, Ahimsaka, that which is not born does not die.

421
00:33:00,582 --> 00:33:04,968
It is not created, nor can it be found, where there's earth, fire, water or air.

422
00:33:05,248 --> 00:33:08,913
It cannot be seen or heard or in any way perceived.

423
00:33:09,673 --> 00:33:12,336
It is the deathless, the unconditioned.

424
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:20,768
If this were not so, there would be no escape from birth, sickness, ageing and death and the endless, endless rounds of rebirth.

425
00:33:23,026 --> 00:33:31,616
Suddenly I heard myself asking, you would accept me, Angulimala, a criminal, a murderer, as your disciple?

426
00:33:33,318 --> 00:33:37,404
You can stop, Bhamsaka, as I have stopped, he replied.

427
00:33:39,667 --> 00:33:46,856
A huge burden seemed to lift, and an enormous joy, born of hope, settled upon me.

428
00:33:50,481 --> 00:33:54,307
First he said you must bury the tools of your abhorrent profession.

429
00:33:54,768 --> 00:33:59,115
You must no longer harm any living being, not even a cockroach.

430
00:34:01,778 --> 00:34:09,431
For the last time, I caressed the beautifully wrought weapons, especially the slender blade with its snake-embraced handle.

431
00:34:11,333 --> 00:34:12,434
I stabbed out a trench.

432
00:34:13,376 --> 00:34:18,244
There I placed these precious jewels, gleaming and glistening in the noonday sun.

433
00:34:19,152 --> 00:34:22,760
how difficult it is to give up an addiction, an obsession.

434
00:34:24,425 --> 00:34:31,643
I forced my hands to cover them with soil and placed heavy boulders on them until I felt sure that I truly buried them and for good.

435
00:34:33,579 --> 00:34:36,925
Then he asked me to go in search for suitable robe cloth.

436
00:34:37,507 --> 00:34:38,429
It's cemeteries.

437
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:57,664
Oh, disturbing places, charnel grounds, corpses steaming the air with their sickly, sweet, pungent stench, dismembered limbs, half eaten by tigers, rodents, vultures, and strewn around the white shrouds that mourners had wrapped their dead in.

438
00:35:02,014 --> 00:35:07,664
about to wash the cloth, when my teacher told me I hadn't yet fully buried the past.

439
00:35:07,684 --> 00:35:08,947
I looked at him, puzzled.

440
00:35:09,728 --> 00:35:10,731
He pointed to a tree.

441
00:35:11,893 --> 00:35:23,213
There, hanging forgotten around my makeshift shrine to Kali, was the garland of finger bones, gently swaying in the sighing breeze, their chimes hollow and choked.

442
00:35:24,947 --> 00:35:29,793
I laid them down in a circle, each finger pointing inward to the now empty pit.

443
00:35:31,155 --> 00:35:41,467
And on the burial mound over these sacred bodies, I planted a frangipani tree, whose white, sweet, perfumed flowers would ever shower their sad grave.

444
00:35:43,969 --> 00:35:51,478
I watched over this cemetery, recalling their murders, begging forgiveness, till sleep overpowered me.

445
00:35:55,592 --> 00:35:59,697
The next day I washed the white cloth, and with my teacher's needle and thread made robes.

446
00:36:00,278 --> 00:36:05,764
He then shaved my head and beard, and finally all was ready for me to make my request.

447
00:36:07,407 --> 00:36:09,429
Bhagava, may you be my guide.

448
00:36:10,391 --> 00:36:12,472
I shall live dependent on the Bhagava.

449
00:36:13,693 --> 00:36:19,221
Come, he replied, and conduct yourself diligently according to the customs of ascetics.

450
00:36:21,226 --> 00:36:30,177
That evening, for the first time, bliss was the object of my meditation.

451
00:36:30,197 --> 00:36:33,541
The following day, he wanted to return to his monastery in Esavathi.

452
00:36:34,722 --> 00:36:35,623
He sensed my fear.

453
00:36:36,844 --> 00:36:40,550
I will not recognize you, he assured me, knowing how different I looked.

454
00:36:42,030 --> 00:36:44,994
When we arrived at the first village, there were shouts of recognition.

455
00:36:45,635 --> 00:36:46,677
Bhagavad Gautama!

456
00:36:47,585 --> 00:36:49,106
A great thrill passed through my body.

457
00:36:49,246 --> 00:36:50,869
I'd only heard of this great teacher.

458
00:36:50,929 --> 00:36:52,510
I couldn't believe my good fortune.

459
00:36:54,213 --> 00:36:58,958
The villagers told their tales of Angulimala and how they thirsted for revenge.

460
00:37:00,221 --> 00:37:03,605
Ah, said the Bhagavad, your revenge makes you no better than he.

461
00:37:04,567 --> 00:37:05,728
Let the king deal with him.

462
00:37:06,168 --> 00:37:07,170
Oh, the law of karma.

463
00:37:08,070 --> 00:37:11,735
Better to live good lives and offer your merit to your departed loved ones.

464
00:37:12,195 --> 00:37:13,358
That is what they need.

465
00:37:15,661 --> 00:37:16,782
None recognized me.

466
00:37:17,032 --> 00:37:22,778
As a young, clean-shaven disciple, it was proper for me to keep my eyes lowered and remain silent.

467
00:37:23,980 --> 00:37:25,762
He asked them to help me dye my robes.

468
00:37:28,126 --> 00:37:30,989
That evening I approached the Bhagavata in ochre robes.

469
00:37:31,789 --> 00:37:34,373
I knelt before him and asked him for a name.

470
00:37:35,735 --> 00:37:38,737
You shall be known by the name of your innocent childhood, he said.

471
00:37:40,740 --> 00:37:44,085
I was to be known as Bhikkhu Ahimsaka, the Harmless One.

472
00:37:46,123 --> 00:37:48,748
That day all the villagers took a day away from their labours.

473
00:37:49,568 --> 00:37:54,615
He talked both to the group and to the individual, calming and consoling them.

474
00:37:54,635 --> 00:38:01,907
And so we continued, staying at village after village, until we saw ahead of us the walls of the capital city, Savathi.

475
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:13,684
The monastery, on the outskirts of the city...

476
00:38:14,052 --> 00:38:21,521
It was a set of buildings with a large meditation hall, neat footpaths, bushes, flowers and trees bordering well-kept lawns.

477
00:38:22,262 --> 00:38:25,485
Everyone stood waiting, hands joined before them in Anjali.

478
00:38:25,947 --> 00:38:28,389
They greeted him with silence and smiles.

479
00:38:29,610 --> 00:38:36,699
I was shown to a hut hidden in the tamed forest grove close by, a sturdy little bamboo affair covered in layers of banana leaves.

480
00:38:37,460 --> 00:38:40,465
No more than two good strides in length and one in breadth,

481
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:44,204
I had that strange feeling of coming home.

482
00:38:46,427 --> 00:38:58,222
I lay there that night on the soft-platted palm-leaf mat, listening to the crickets and the conversation of owls, musing how my life had so quickly turned around.

483
00:38:59,384 --> 00:39:01,085
Truly miraculous.

484
00:39:04,929 --> 00:39:13,063
During the first few days I would constantly visit the bhagava, but his attendant, the elder Ananda, would always tell me to go back to my hut and practice.

485
00:39:14,025 --> 00:39:15,467
I felt annoyed and frustrated.

486
00:39:15,507 --> 00:39:18,713
Then one day the bhagava asked to see me.

487
00:39:20,277 --> 00:39:25,065
Dear friend, he said, it's not proper to develop an affection for the teacher.

488
00:39:25,382 --> 00:39:27,905
I can't bring about your deliverance from suffering.

489
00:39:28,306 --> 00:39:33,092
You must take refuge in the teachings and the practice, but above all in yourself.

490
00:39:33,853 --> 00:39:34,914
I can only point the way.

491
00:39:35,815 --> 00:39:38,438
So please don't come unless called.

492
00:39:39,940 --> 00:39:43,943
That day I felt utterly dejected, abandoned.

493
00:39:43,963 --> 00:39:50,090
So much so, I even began to dream of being Angulimala, and all the pleasures of hunting assailed me.

494
00:39:51,893 --> 00:40:01,085
I was guided skillfully, and I came to realize that it was this craving to be teacher's best boy that had so angered my fellow students.

495
00:40:02,226 --> 00:40:03,126
I was a creep.

496
00:40:10,697 --> 00:40:15,722
Then, early one morning, there were drums, and the occasional salute of trumpets.

497
00:40:16,443 --> 00:40:18,626
The king and his army are en route somewhere.

498
00:40:19,972 --> 00:40:22,896
To my horror, I suddenly realized they were coming to the monastery.

499
00:40:23,297 --> 00:40:24,619
You can imagine my alarm.

500
00:40:25,701 --> 00:40:32,190
I'd all but decided to run away when a young monk came and told me to come at once.

501
00:40:32,210 --> 00:40:36,097
As I entered the Bhagavad's room, he saw the look of anxiety on my face and smiled.

502
00:40:36,777 --> 00:40:39,822
With an insistent gesture, he motioned me to sit by him.

503
00:40:41,101 --> 00:40:43,864
We sat and waited as the marching footsteps approached us.

504
00:40:44,806 --> 00:40:51,978
And suddenly at the door stood the king, a short, stocky, heavily bearded man, the warrior in his eyes.

505
00:40:53,981 --> 00:40:56,525
The king and his officers paid homage to the bhagava.

506
00:40:57,266 --> 00:40:59,590
I knew all of them, though none recognized me.

507
00:41:00,210 --> 00:41:02,134
In mind, I did keep my head low.

508
00:41:03,456 --> 00:41:06,501
After the usual pleasantries were exchanged, the king explained.

509
00:41:06,902 --> 00:41:09,726
Yeah, they've come for your blessing, Bhagavan.

510
00:41:09,746 --> 00:41:11,628
It's this Angulimala.

511
00:41:12,628 --> 00:41:15,311
I've sent out dozens of platoons, but to no avail.

512
00:41:16,032 --> 00:41:19,255
He's murdered hundreds, wiped out whole villages.

513
00:41:19,356 --> 00:41:19,956
Extraordinary.

514
00:41:20,876 --> 00:41:23,079
But how to deal with a deranged madman?

515
00:41:23,300 --> 00:41:25,621
Why is he collecting fingers?

516
00:41:26,902 --> 00:41:28,525
There came a burst of suggestions.

517
00:41:28,545 --> 00:41:29,166
He's possessed.

518
00:41:29,405 --> 00:41:29,806
A demon.

519
00:41:30,047 --> 00:41:30,567
A lunatic.

520
00:41:31,568 --> 00:41:34,311
When the excitement had calmed, the Bhagavan said,

521
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:40,027
What would you say, your majesty, if such a dark-hearted murderer were to become a monk?

522
00:41:41,230 --> 00:41:43,132
I could feel the panic rising in me.

523
00:41:43,755 --> 00:41:44,014
What?

524
00:41:44,376 --> 00:41:47,181
shouted the king, his mouth agape with incredulity.

525
00:41:47,802 --> 00:41:50,067
A chorus of scoffing supported his scorn.

526
00:41:50,768 --> 00:41:53,333
Don't be so dismissive, urged the Bhagavan.

527
00:41:53,693 --> 00:41:56,940
Even this Angulimala can transform himself.

528
00:41:57,106 --> 00:41:58,286
Transform himself?

529
00:41:58,807 --> 00:42:00,028
The king continued to shout.

530
00:42:00,510 --> 00:42:02,371
When I catch him, I'll transform him.

531
00:42:02,452 --> 00:42:03,713
I'll have him roasted alive.

532
00:42:04,393 --> 00:42:07,996
There were great guffaws and equally delicious torments suggested.

533
00:42:08,657 --> 00:42:10,960
But one especially made my hair stand on end.

534
00:42:12,021 --> 00:42:17,067
I'd have him slowly cut to pieces so that he could watch his body being eaten by dogs.

535
00:42:18,889 --> 00:42:21,110
It wasn't the horror of it, but the voice.

536
00:42:21,992 --> 00:42:26,876
It was that childhood enemy, Vajiro, now an officer in the king's guard.

537
00:42:29,184 --> 00:42:32,347
Do you really think that revenge can ever be satisfied?

538
00:42:33,068 --> 00:42:36,771
Whatever you do, the bereaved will complain it wasn't harsh enough.

539
00:42:37,693 --> 00:42:39,614
Violence breeds violence.

540
00:42:40,076 --> 00:42:41,978
It can only be attained by compassion.

541
00:42:42,617 --> 00:42:44,400
This is an ancient law.

542
00:42:46,461 --> 00:42:47,822
There was an uneasy silence.

543
00:42:49,224 --> 00:42:50,806
You did come for my advice.

544
00:42:52,088 --> 00:42:53,027
Again that smile.

545
00:42:54,590 --> 00:42:56,552
The king looked around at his company.

546
00:42:56,572 --> 00:42:57,672
Everyone was baffled.

547
00:42:58,362 --> 00:43:02,766
"'So you want us to catch him and bring him to you, Bhagavad?'

548
00:43:02,786 --> 00:43:03,567
suggested the king.

549
00:43:03,586 --> 00:43:05,668
"'No need for that.'

550
00:43:05,688 --> 00:43:13,034
"'And turning to me, the Bhagavad cheerfully announced, "'Here he is, Angulimala, now Bhikkhu Ahimsaka.'

551
00:43:13,054 --> 00:43:19,340
"'The whole company, to a man including the king, instinctively grabbed their swords.

552
00:43:20,081 --> 00:43:21,362
"'There was a stunned silence.

553
00:43:22,503 --> 00:43:23,425
"'Perhaps you know him?'

554
00:43:24,025 --> 00:43:25,606
asked the Bhagavad.

555
00:43:25,626 --> 00:43:27,188
"'I looked up in surprise.'

556
00:43:27,909 --> 00:43:28,931
The king glared at me.

557
00:43:30,695 --> 00:43:34,581
Ahimsaka, he said at first in shock, and then in growing surprise.

558
00:43:35,101 --> 00:43:37,806
Ahimsaka, son of Gaga and Montani.

559
00:43:39,510 --> 00:43:41,713
He related the circumstances of my birth.

560
00:43:42,996 --> 00:43:45,800
But why, he asked, why the fingers?

561
00:43:47,248 --> 00:43:50,153
I then told him about the gift demanded by my guru.

562
00:43:50,534 --> 00:43:54,701
Realizing my predicament, a sympathy grew towards me among the king and his company.

563
00:43:54,940 --> 00:43:58,485
Indeed, I could see sadness shadow the king's face.

564
00:44:00,809 --> 00:44:10,405
After a long pause in which the king kept looking at me and then to the bhagava, he said, You're a lucky man, Bhikkhu Ahimsaka, a very lucky man.

565
00:44:12,409 --> 00:44:13,672
With that they began to leave.

566
00:44:14,673 --> 00:44:20,003
But the king, as he reached the door, turned and warned me not to leave the Bhagavata's order.

567
00:44:22,027 --> 00:44:23,510
We listened to the marching steps.

568
00:44:24,972 --> 00:44:26,896
The Bhagavata turned to me and smiled.

569
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,684
I took a very deep breath.

570
00:44:40,927 --> 00:44:46,795
The very next morning, as I was preparing to go on alms round, there was a knock at my door.

571
00:44:49,880 --> 00:44:53,286
I opened it to find what I most dreaded standing before me.

572
00:44:54,427 --> 00:44:54,967
My mother.

573
00:44:55,949 --> 00:44:58,552
Was a basket of food enough for an elephant?

574
00:44:58,572 --> 00:45:04,161
Here and then I began to sob, to sob uncontrollably.

575
00:45:05,322 --> 00:45:10,851
No doubt she thought it was remorse for the shame that I'd brought upon the family, not the sobbing.

576
00:45:12,771 --> 00:45:20,460
Not so many days ago, I was stalking this very woman, intent on stabbing her through the heart, slicing off her finger.

577
00:45:21,581 --> 00:45:28,911
This woman, my mother, who bore me, suckled me, tended to my every care.

578
00:45:30,813 --> 00:45:34,016
My heart cramped into a solid spasm of agony.

579
00:45:36,739 --> 00:45:42,407
If ever I were to describe hell, it would be the heart-wrenching compunction I felt that day

580
00:45:45,661 --> 00:45:48,925
Happily, even hell passes.

581
00:45:50,025 --> 00:45:55,532
But this was the bloodiest of daggers I'd pierced into my own heart.

582
00:45:55,552 --> 00:46:03,362
I told her my tale, and of the king's stipulation not to leave the Order, and that I needed time to cure the festering in my heart.

583
00:46:04,364 --> 00:46:05,664
I sensed her disappointment.

584
00:46:06,186 --> 00:46:09,750
She'd wanted grandchildren and all that.

585
00:46:09,769 --> 00:46:12,833
And as for my father, he wasn't surprised, of course.

586
00:46:13,054 --> 00:46:14,436
Hadn't he foretold it?

587
00:46:15,478 --> 00:46:20,023
It was that I had become a disciple of someone who wasn't a Brahmin that he found offensive.

588
00:46:21,525 --> 00:46:23,387
Eventually, he offered me his blessing.

589
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,452
Not everyone came to accept me, of course.

590
00:46:28,273 --> 00:46:33,277
On arms round, children poked fun at me, making up silly songs about Angulimala.

591
00:46:33,297 --> 00:46:37,663
But more serious, people threw stones at me, some bouncing off my head.

592
00:46:39,244 --> 00:46:40,146
I'd just walk on.

593
00:46:40,585 --> 00:46:42,128
They would eventually tire.

594
00:46:43,998 --> 00:46:46,460
but I was attacked viciously once.

595
00:46:46,481 --> 00:46:57,275
A few of the aggrieved families whipped up a crowd to such a righteous frenzy that they beat me with sticks and were taking me out of the city to kill me, when the guards at the gates stopped them.

596
00:46:57,295 --> 00:47:00,500
Ironically, it was Vajiro in command of the post.

597
00:47:01,422 --> 00:47:09,251
With a great look of disdain, he ordered a platoon of soldiers to escort me back to the monastery.

598
00:47:09,271 --> 00:47:13,498
It took days for the bruises to heal, but luckily there were no broken bones.

599
00:47:14,878 --> 00:47:40,835
saying to myself if this is all the karma I have to suffer how fortunate indeed it was on one of these arms rounds that something quite remarkable happened I'd stopped in front of a house in case someone should want to offer food

600
00:47:41,068 --> 00:47:42,311
when I heard great cries.

601
00:47:43,092 --> 00:47:47,882
A man came out, looking desperate, saw me, and shouted, This is no time to come begging.

602
00:47:47,943 --> 00:47:49,005
Can't you hear my wife?

603
00:47:50,568 --> 00:47:53,735
Her cries resurrected the screams of my victims.

604
00:47:55,137 --> 00:47:57,643
I was so depressed by this that I went to see the bug of her.

605
00:47:59,210 --> 00:48:02,715
Go back and offer this blessing, he said.

606
00:48:02,755 --> 00:48:11,088
Say, by the power of a harmless life, let that mother's pain cease and the child be born safe.

607
00:48:12,490 --> 00:48:14,653
Harmless life, I said incredulously.

608
00:48:15,514 --> 00:48:20,543
Since your spiritual life began, from the day of your ordination, the bugger replied.

609
00:48:22,159 --> 00:48:28,266
Yes, I thought, at least I could make an offering of my harmless life, albeit a little short.

610
00:48:29,588 --> 00:48:34,534
How wonderful if I could actually assist a birth, I who had assisted so many deaths.

611
00:48:37,038 --> 00:48:39,179
She was still crying out and praying to the gods.

612
00:48:39,740 --> 00:48:41,402
Quite a crowd had gathered outside the house.

613
00:48:41,663 --> 00:48:43,666
I stood at the gates and offered my blessing.

614
00:48:44,786 --> 00:48:52,115
Sister, since I was born into the noble life, I do not recall having ever intentionally killed a living being.

615
00:48:52,382 --> 00:48:57,108
By this truth may you be well and may your child be safe.

616
00:48:57,911 --> 00:48:59,432
Everyone began to scoff and jeer.

617
00:48:59,452 --> 00:49:02,036
I could feel the anger rising.

618
00:49:02,135 --> 00:49:02,936
I left at once.

619
00:49:04,259 --> 00:49:08,105
That evening the clamour of a crowd approached my hut and called for me.

620
00:49:08,865 --> 00:49:09,907
I began to panic again.

621
00:49:10,628 --> 00:49:12,550
I took a deep breath and opened the door.

622
00:49:14,914 --> 00:49:17,918
And there before me stood a man holding a baby.

623
00:49:19,197 --> 00:49:22,481
There were shouts of Saru, Saru, Saru, well done.

624
00:49:23,362 --> 00:49:28,849
Presents were laid before me and a garland of the most beautiful white frangipani was placed around my neck.

625
00:49:29,929 --> 00:49:37,460
They told me that almost immediately after my blessing, the baby was born and both mother and child were well.

626
00:49:37,480 --> 00:49:39,242
I was to be honoured guest at the feast.

627
00:49:40,784 --> 00:49:43,246
It was all I could do to blubber my thanks.

628
00:49:44,914 --> 00:49:50,184
Oh, to my surprise, my chant has become a magical mantra for mothers to be.

629
00:49:51,146 --> 00:49:55,753
And from that day on, the children stopped poking fun.

630
00:49:55,773 --> 00:50:01,923
Coarse words became kindly greetings, and the stones turned into flowers, incense, and sweets.

631
00:50:03,666 --> 00:50:07,833
My heart ached with relief and joy at their forgiveness.

632
00:50:19,153 --> 00:50:30,313
After many years, once I felt sure enough in my practice, I decided to go to the neighbouring kingdom of Magadha, where no one would recognise me, in order to live a more solitary life.

633
00:50:31,514 --> 00:50:36,023
I found a secluded forest, not far from the prosperous capital of Rajagaha.

634
00:50:37,025 --> 00:50:40,911
It was the dry, hot season, so I made my home beneath a great shady fig tree.

635
00:50:41,572 --> 00:50:44,858
In time, the villagers generously built me a hut.

636
00:50:46,811 --> 00:50:51,677
There I continued to work, work hard, through all the mental anguish.

637
00:50:53,358 --> 00:50:59,266
There were the burning hurts and scorching revenge towards my enemies, especially my guru.

638
00:51:00,327 --> 00:51:15,603
It stung to know, to find out, that he had believed the malicious slander that I had been scheming to have him removed so that I could take his prestigious post, and that he had given me such a heinous obligation out of hateful spite.

639
00:51:17,221 --> 00:51:26,072
Then there was the nauseous guilt and agonising remorse towards my victims, as well as all the usual unquenchable lusts, paralysing fears and so on.

640
00:51:26,954 --> 00:51:28,114
Oh, I thought they'd never end.

641
00:51:29,777 --> 00:51:34,443
And yet, over the years, everything began to subside.

642
00:51:36,106 --> 00:51:38,668
And in the clearings it became so obvious.

643
00:51:39,690 --> 00:51:42,634
No one had actually ever made me suffer.

644
00:51:42,954 --> 00:51:43,835
No one.

645
00:51:44,137 --> 00:51:50,063
Not the plots of my enemies, not the punches of Agiro, not even the vicious malevolence of my guru.

646
00:51:51,144 --> 00:51:54,730
All the ensuing hurt and hate was of my own making.

647
00:51:55,710 --> 00:51:58,534
Was it not my own befuddled thinking that led me to murder?

648
00:51:59,514 --> 00:52:03,539
The demonic delight I took in killing, was that not mine to develop?

649
00:52:03,900 --> 00:52:07,605
And all the self-pity, self-hatred, guilt, remorse, and so on, and so on, and so on.

650
00:52:07,925 --> 00:52:09,947
Was that not all direct consequence?

651
00:52:11,349 --> 00:52:12,590
All the time I was blaming it,

652
00:52:13,599 --> 00:52:16,143
Wittingly, I was creating my own hell.

653
00:52:16,943 --> 00:52:25,693
And so it was that since none had actually caused me to suffer, I lost all reason, all need to forgive anyone.

654
00:52:25,713 --> 00:52:28,016
And it was then I saw as clear as day.

655
00:52:28,617 --> 00:52:37,146
But for mistaken understanding, deluded reasoning, I had never actually meant any harm, never meant to cause anyone any suffering whatsoever.

656
00:52:37,507 --> 00:52:42,813
And so it was that I lost all reason, all need to be forgiven.

657
00:52:44,092 --> 00:52:50,463
I was like a man who, wandering through a forest, kicks a crooked stick only to disturb a viper.

658
00:52:50,483 --> 00:52:53,887
Just because he's mistaken doesn't mean he and others won't be bitten.

659
00:52:56,251 --> 00:53:10,032
Is this not a great paradox of human life that we are at once responsible for our moral behaviour, yet because we are fundamentally not immoral, not bad, not evil, but ignorant, mistaken, deluded...

660
00:53:10,704 --> 00:53:13,628
were therefore intrinsically innocent.

661
00:53:14,449 --> 00:53:17,574
Indeed, if this were not so, how could we ever attain purity?

662
00:53:18,414 --> 00:53:21,880
And without purity, there can be no liberation from suffering.

663
00:53:25,644 --> 00:53:28,369
These insights came early one morning.

664
00:53:29,911 --> 00:53:37,641
From my hut, perched on the side of a wooded valley, I watched the sun rising through the golden air,

665
00:53:38,818 --> 00:53:43,684
full of sweet early monsoon blossom and the trill of songbirds.

666
00:53:45,746 --> 00:53:49,389
And there arose in me such relief and release.

667
00:53:51,413 --> 00:53:54,416
And I remembered how the Bhagavad had answered me on the killing road.

668
00:53:55,956 --> 00:53:59,782
I have stopped, Angulimala.

669
00:53:59,842 --> 00:54:02,003
Now, I've stopped too.

670
00:54:03,565 --> 00:54:04,827
I've done what had to be done.

671
00:54:06,291 --> 00:54:26,358
My heart is purified of all defilements and I live in utter contentment and peace.

